-- Russian Beef, Pork and Poultry Production Increased in April
-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 2013-06-05T12:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-05/russian-beef-pork-and-poultry-production-increased-in-april.html
Russian production of beef, pork and
poultry increased in April from a year earlier, according to
government figures.  Output gained 34 percent to 104,000 metric tons for pork
and 18 percent to 16,300 tons for beef and meat from other
cattle, the Federal State Statistics Service, known as Rosstat,
said in an e-mailed statement today. Production of poultry and
its byproducts climbed 6.9 percent to 302,000 tons.  Cattle and poultry production by so-called live weight,
which includes skin, bones and byproducts, rose 9.7 percent to
900,000 tons, according to Rosstat.  Russiaâ€™s cattle herd fell 1.2 percent from a year earlier
to 20.9 million head by the end of April and the number of cows
dropped 1.8 percent to 8.9 million, the statement showed. Hogs
gained 8.6 percent to 20.2 million animals and the number of
sheep and goats advanced 1.8 percent to 26.4 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
